 {debugFlag}LoadTatinAndStartServer flag
⍝ This function is called when the batch tests require an instance of Dyalog running a Tatin Server.
⍝ `flag` is just insurance against an accidental call.
⍝ `debugFlag` is optional and defaults to 0. 1 basically switched error trapping off.
 :If flag
     debugFlag←{0<⎕NC ⍵:⍎⍵ ⋄ 0}'debugFlag'
     {}⎕SE.Link.Import'#.Tatin' './APLSource'
     #.Tatin.TestCasesServer.RunBatchTests debugFlag
 :EndIf
⍝Done
